<section class="section"><div class="wrap"><div class="section-head"><p class="eyebrow">Why Leicester</p><h2>Everything is here. The Week puts it on one stage.</h2><p>Research excellence, business infrastructure and public reach already exist across the city. The Week connects them in one unmistakable programme.</p></div><div class="proof-grid"><article class="proof"><span class="num">01 — Heritage</span><h3>65 years in orbit</h3><p>The University of Leicester’s first instrument flew in 1961. A Leicester-built presence in space has continued since 1967.</p></article><article class="proof"><span class="num">02 — Infrastructure</span><h3>A working Space City</h3><p>Space Park Leicester is a live hub for research, industry and enterprise—built with university, industry and government.</p></article><article class="proof"><span class="num">03 — Momentum</span><h3>A growth priority</h3><p>Space and Earth observation are recognised regional beacon sectors, creating a powerful moment to connect people and opportunity.</p></article></div></div></section>
